HEADWORD: Persulphocyanic
<hw>Per*sul`pho*cy*an"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, a yellow
crystalline substance (called also <xex>perthiocyanic acid</xex>),
analogous to sulphocyanic acid, but containing more sulphur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persulphocyanogen</ent>⟦br⟧
